57using WebKitEncodedFrameTiming = EncodedImage::Timing;
58struct WebKitEncodedFrameInfo {
59 uint32_t width { 0 };
60 uint32_t height { 0 };
61 int64_t timeStamp { 0 };
62 int64_t ntpTimeMS { 0 };
63 int64_t captureTimeMS { 0 };
64 VideoFrameType frameType { VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameDelta };
65 VideoRotation rotation { kVideoRotation_0 };
66 VideoContentType contentType { VideoContentType::UNSPECIFIED };
67 bool completeFrame = false;
68 int qp { -1 };
69 WebKitEncodedFrameTiming timing;
70
71 template<class Encoder> void encode(Encoder&) const;
72 template<class Decoder> static bool decode(Decoder&, WebKitEncodedFrameInfo&);
73};

85template<class Decoder>
86bool WebKitEncodedFrameInfo::decode(Decoder& decoder, WebKitEncodedFrameInfo& info)
87{
88 if (!decoder.decode(info.width))
89 return false;
90 if (!decoder.decode(info.height))
91 return false;
92 if (!decoder.decode(info.timeStamp))
93 return false;
94 if (!decoder.decode(info.ntpTimeMS))
95 return false;
96 if (!decoder.decode(info.captureTimeMS))
97 return false;
98 if (!decoder.decode(info.frameType))
99 return false;
100 if (!decoder.decode(info.rotation))
101 return false;
102 if (!decoder.decode(info.contentType))
103 return false;
104 if (!decoder.decode(info.completeFrame))
105 return false;
106 if (!decoder.decode(info.qp))
107 return false;
108
109 if (!decoder.decode(info.timing.flags))
110 return false;
111 if (!decoder.decode(info.timing.encode_start_ms))
112 return false;
113 if (!decoder.decode(info.timing.encode_finish_ms))
114 return false;
115 if (!decoder.decode(info.timing.packetization_finish_ms))
116 return false;
117 if (!decoder.decode(info.timing.pacer_exit_ms))
118 return false;
119 if (!decoder.decode(info.timing.network_timestamp_ms))
120 return false;
121 if (!decoder.decode(info.timing.network2_timestamp_ms))
122 return false;
123 if (!decoder.decode(info.timing.receive_start_ms))
124 return false;
125 if (!decoder.decode(info.timing.receive_finish_ms))
126 return false;
127
128 return true;
129}
130
131template<class Encoder>
132void WebKitEncodedFrameInfo::encode(Encoder& encoder) const
133{
134 encoder << width;
135 encoder << height;
136 encoder << timeStamp;
137 encoder << ntpTimeMS;
138 encoder << captureTimeMS;
139 encoder << frameType;
140 encoder << rotation;
141 encoder << contentType;
142 encoder << completeFrame;
143 encoder << qp;
144
145 encoder << timing.flags;
146 encoder << timing.encode_start_ms;
147 encoder << timing.encode_finish_ms;
148 encoder << timing.packetization_finish_ms;
149 encoder << timing.pacer_exit_ms;
150 encoder << timing.network_timestamp_ms;
151 encoder << timing.network2_timestamp_ms;
152 encoder << timing.receive_start_ms;
153 encoder << timing.receive_finish_ms;
154}
